guid></item><item><title>大脑在麻醉状态下处理无意中听到的单词，但可能不记得它们</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-brain-processes-overheard-words-under-anesthesia-but-it-may-not-remember-them</link><description>一项针对接受癫痫手术的人的研究表明，当人们处于全身麻醉状态时，海马体可能会处理单词和言语，即使研究参与者不记得它们&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-brain-processes-overheard-words-under-anesthesia-but-it-may-not-remember-them.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 12:06:47 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-brain-processes-overheard-words-under-anesthesia-but-it-may-not-remember-them</guid></item><item><title>人工智能教父：如何打造安全的超级智能人工智能</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/godfather-of-ai-how-to-make-safe-superintelligent-ai</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 11:51:47 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/godfather-of-ai-how-to-make-safe-superintelligent-ai</guid></item><item><title>富人资助科学对每个人都有好处</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/wealthy-individuals-funding-science-is-good-for-everyone</link><description>关于私人资助对尖端科学的重要性的优秀文章。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/wealthy-individuals-funding-science-is-good-for-everyone3.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 11:36:47 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/wealthy-individuals-funding-science-is-good-for-everyone</guid></item><item><title>Kanvas 使微生物组成为药物——其影响是巨大的</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/kanvas-makes-the-microbiome-druggable-and-the-implications-are-massive</link><description>坎瓦斯看起来棒极了！他们正在系统地解读微生物组并开发临床阶段的干预措施，以改善肿瘤学及其他领域的患者治疗结果。非常令人印象深刻！我还对他们针对孕产妇环境肠功能障碍 (EED) 的方法特别感兴趣，该疾病显然影响着 1.5 亿人！ &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/kanvas-makes-the-microbiome-druggable-and-the-implications-are-massive.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 11:21:47 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/kanvas-makes-the-microbiome-druggable-and-the-implications-are-massive</guid></item><item><title>一种脂肪可能会加速大脑衰老，但科学家表示有解决办法</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/one-type-of-fat-may-accelerate-brain-aging-but-scientists-say-theres-a-fix</link><description>一项新的研究表明，器官周围聚集的脂肪水平较高与大脑老化速度加快有关，而葡萄糖和胰岛素可能是调节因素。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/one-type-of-fat-may-accelerate-brain-aging-but-scientists-say-theres-a-fix.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 11:06:47 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/one-type-of-fat-may-accelerate-brain-aging-but-scientists-say-theres-a-fix</guid></item><item><title>专门的RNA分子可以对抗ALS神经退行性变</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/specialized-rna-molecules-could-counter-als-neurodegeneration</link><description>畸形蛋白质会带来一系列麻烦，尤其是在神经退行性疾病中。但一项新的研究表明，给他们一点额外的支持可能会让他们保持正常工作，甚至扭转他们造成的损害。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/specialized-rna-molecules-could-counter-als-neurodegeneration2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 10:51:47 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/specialized-rna-molecules-could-counter-als-neurodegeneration</guid></item><item><title>通过非对称谐振超材料中的气缝控制动态可调奇异态</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/dynamically-tunable-singular-states-through-air-slit-control-in-asymmetric-resonant-metamaterials</link><description>这项研究提出了一种使用基于空气狭缝的结构修改来动态调整一维（1D）光子晶格（PL）中奇异态的新方法。由对称破缺引起的共振辐射产生的奇异态，通过共振模式和背景辐射之间的相互作用产生不同的光谱特征。通过策略性地结合空气狭缝来打破一维 PL 中的对称性，我们展示了对谐振位置的有效控制，从而实现了包括窄带带通和陷波滤波在内的双重功能。这些奇异态源自不对称导模谐振（aGMR），可以通过等效平板波导的分析模型来解释。此外，多个空气狭缝的引入通过在共振带中诱导多重折叠行为显着增强了光谱可调性。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/dynamically-tunable-singular-states-through-air-slit-control-in-asymmetric-resonant-metamaterials2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 10:36:47 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/dynamically-tunable-singular-states-through-air-slit-control-in-asymmetric-resonant-metamaterials</guid></item></channel></rss>